Moral stories in English are stories that teach a lesson or a value through an example or a situation12.Some examples of moral stories in English are12:
The Lion and the Mouse: A mouse helps a lion escape from a trap and the lion returns the favor later. Moral: Kindness is never wasted.
The Ant and the Grasshopper: An ant works hard to store food for winter while a grasshopper plays and mocks the ant. When winter comes, the ant has enough food while the grasshopper starves. Moral: There is a time for work and a time for play.
The Boy and the Starfish: A boy saves many starfish from dying by throwing them back into the sea. A man tells him that his effort is futile, but the boy says that he made a difference for each starfish he saved. Moral: Every small act of kindness matters.